  "prompt": "What is the definition of potential energy?",
  "response": "Potential energy is the energy that an object possesses due to its position, condition, or configuration. It is the energy stored within an object, which has the potential to do work in the future. There are various forms of potential energy, such as gravitational potential energy, which depends on an object's height and mass; elastic potential energy, which is stored in objects that can be stretched or compressed, like springs; and chemical potential energy, which is stored in the bonds of atoms and molecules.",
